#	This file contains config info for /config/ra_thresholds object.
#	The format for the file is defined as:
#	The line starting with # defines comment

#	The first noncommented line is expected to be "version" number.
#	Every Threshold information should start with the identifier 
#	RA_Threshold:(The word is case sensitive).

# 	The next line after the Threshold identifier should be 
#	ThresholdName, ObjType, DateRangeType(0 or 1 or 2), WeekDay(1-7), 
#	OffsetTime(In 24Hr Format eg:21:00,9:30), 
#	Threshold Length(in  Hours or Minutes or Seconds) and the value
#	should be less than the number of seconds in a week    	

#	DateRangeType of 0 indicates Period Alert.
#	DateRangeType of 1 indicates Day Alert.
#	DateRangeType of 2 indicates Weekly Alert.

#	WeekDay 1-7 indicates sunday - saturday
#	WeekDay is 0 for Day Alert.

#	The Length of Period should be followed by Secs/Mins/Hrs Identifier

#	The next line should be either Filter details or Field_Value_Range 
#	details with the correspondig identifier 
#	RA_Filter: and  RA_Field_Value_Range:(Both case sensitive). 

#	Filter details Array is optional while Field_Value_Range details is 
#	mandatory. 

#	Always Filter details should precced Field_Value_Range_Details
#	The filter fields should have FilterFieldName, FilterIntValue, 
#	FilterStringValue (in the same order)

#	The Field Value Range fields should have RangeFieldName, MaxFieldValue,
#	MinFieldValue (in the same order)
#	The field delimiter in a line may be space or tab.

#	A sample format is given below
#	No space or tab is allowed in the same field (eg 21: 30 is invalid)

#  RA_Threshold:
#  <Threshold Name>  <Obj Type> <Date Range Type> <WeekDay> <Number of Units>  <Start Offset>  <Length of Period > <Secs/Mins/Hrs>

#	RA_Filter:	
#		<Filter Field Name>	<Filter Int Value>	<Filter String Value>
#		<Filter Field Name>	<Filter Int Value>	<Filter String Value>
#		<Filter Field Name>	<Filter Int Value>	<Filter String Value>
#	RA_Field_Value_Range:
#		<Field Name>		<Max_Field_Value>	<Min_Field_Value>
#		<Field Name>		<Max_Field_Value>	<Min_Field_Value>
#		<Field Name>		<Max_Field_Value>	<Min_Field_Value>


